title: Too-tall truck gets stuck on Soldiers Field Road - Massachusetts news
text:
Well, it wasn’t technically on Storrow Drive, but a too-tall truck got itself “Storrowed” on Monday night.
State police tell Boston.com that troopers responded at 9:50 p.m. Monday to an overheight truck on Soldiers Field Road at the Bay State Road Footbridge.
Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Video of the truck, with its top sheared off, was shared on Twitter by user @thedro14 :
@cbsboston . Another truck crushes an overpass on storrow drive. pic.twitter.com/OwGs4Lieud
— The Dro (@thedro14) October 13, 2015 There were no reports of injuries, and the scene was cleared late Monday night, according to state police.
